{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GxLaWtLbrYmxdBmSo9kiUB","type":"tool_result","content":"26\tpublic interface MainAuthenticationConfigurer {\n27\t\n28\t    void configureAuthentication(AuthenticationConfig authenticationConfig, HttpServerConfigurationProperties properties);\n29\t\n30\t    void configureAuthentication(\n31\t            AuthenticationConfig authenticationConfig, HttpManagementServerConfigurationProperties properties);\n32\t\n33\t    /**\n34\t     * Normalizes the configured authentication path into a wildcard pattern so that authentication is applied to the\n35\t     * configured path <em>and everything beneath it</em>.\n36\t     * <p>\n37\t     * Without this, a non-wildcard path (such as the server context-path or an explicitly configured\n38\t     * {@code authenticationPath}) is registered as an exact-match route, leaving every sub-path reachable without\n39\t     * authentication. That is an authentication bypass using an alternate path (CWE-288).\n40\t     *\n41\t     * @param  path the configured authentication path (may be {@code null} or empty)\n42\t     * @return      a wildcard path that protects the configured path and all sub-paths\n43\t     */\n44\t    static String toAuthenticationPath(String path) {\n45\t        if (path == null || path.isEmpty()) {\n46\t            // protect everything when no path is configured\n47\t            return \"/*\";\n48\t        }\n49\t        if (!path.endsWith(\"*\")) {\n50\t            // turn the path into a prefix match so sub-paths are also authenticated\n51\t            path = path + \"*\";\n52\t        }\n53\t        return path;\n54\t    }\n55\t\n56\t}\n57\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c08ad513-23dd-4852-bceb-3c7b576ec9a3","uuid":"881c25fc-7e9f-4adb-b640-026d1dbb9e8e","timestamp":"2026-06-30T19:31:10.874Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/work/components/camel-platform-http-main/src/main/java/org/apache/camel/component/platform/http/main/authentication/MainAuthenticationConfigurer.java","content":"public interface MainAuthenticationConfigurer {\n\n    void configureAuthentication(AuthenticationConfig authenticationConfig, HttpServerConfigurationProperties properties);\n\n    void configureAuthentication(\n            AuthenticationConfig authenticationConfig, HttpManagementServerConfigurationProperties properties);\n\n    /**\n     * Normalizes the configured authentication path into a wildcard pattern so that authentication is applied to the\n     * configured path <em>and everything beneath it</em>.\n     * <p>\n     * Without this, a non-wildcard path (such as the server context-path or an explicitly configured\n     * {@code authenticationPath}) is registered as an exact-match route, leaving every sub-path reachable without\n     * authentication. That is an authentication bypass using an alternate path (CWE-288).\n     *\n     * @param  path the configured authentication path (may be {@code null} or empty)\n     * @return      a wildcard path that protects the configured path and all sub-paths\n     */\n    static String toAuthenticationPath(String path) {\n        if (path == null || path.isEmpty()) {\n            // protect everything when no path is configured\n            return \"/*\";\n        }\n        if (!path.endsWith(\"*\")) {\n            // turn the path into a prefix match so sub-paths are also authenticated\n            path = path + \"*\";\n        }\n        return path;\n    }\n\n}\n","numLines":32,"startLine":26,"totalLines":57}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_0116bdqZqHUvKDCzFj96bViL","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Summary\n\n**Vulnerability (CWE-288 — Authentication Bypass Using an Alternate Path or Channel):** In the embedded HTTP server authentication configurers, the protected route path was derived from `authenticationPath` (falling back to the server context `path`), but only the exact value `\"/\"` was expanded to the wildcard `\"/*\"`. Any other configured path was registered verbatim as an **exact-match** Vert.x route (`subRouter.route(entry.getPath())`). Because Vert.x exact routes don't match descendants, requests to any sub-path beneath the configured path (e.g. `/secure/data` when protecting `/secure`) reached the application **without authentication** — a classic alternate-path bypass.\n\n**Fix:** Added a single fail-secure normalization helper, `MainAuthenticationConfigurer.toAuthenticationPath(...)`, and routed all four configuration paths (Basic + JWT, each with a main-server and management-server overload) through it. The helper:\n\n- returns `/*` when the path is null/empty (protect everything rather than nothing), and\n- appends `*` to any path not already ending in `*`, turning it into a Vert.x **prefix match** so the configured path **and all sub-paths** are authenticated.\n\n**Behavior preserved:** The common/default case `path = \"/\"` still produces `/*`, and an already-wildcard value like `/*` is left unchanged — identical to before. The change only affects the previously-broken non-root case, closing the bypass on the side of more (not less) authentication. The edits are confined to the three files named in `FINDING.txt`; no commits, pushes, or other changes were made.\n\nI wasn't able to compile-verify because the Maven build needs a network-fetched build extension that's unavailable offline, but the change is plain Java 17 (a `static` interface method invoked from the implementing classes)."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":945,"cache_read_input_tokens":60860,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":945},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c08ad513-23dd-4852-bceb-3c7b576ec9a3","uuid":"557c6201-3512-4ffb-8584-f47fea901840","request_id":"req_011CcZzxxTEqHLWLJCk72hnb"}
